  "timeframe": "15m",
  "market_context": "Post-CPI release session on January 11, 2024. Both ES and NQ rally into a daily fair value gap. NQ takes out the prior high while ES fails to do so, creating an SMT divergence at the FVG. Equal lows rest below as downside liquidity targets.",
  "key_observation": "NQ swept its prior high (creating high resistance liquidity) while ES did not, producing an SMT divergence into a daily FVG. The short candle's structure also formed a breaker block, but with CPI volatility a stop above the high-resistance-liquidity sweep is preferred over the breaker itself.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Observed CPI release and identified that NQ reached the high into the daily fair value gap while ES did not, creating an SMT divergence.",
    "Step 2: Anticipated the high to hold and began looking for a short entry on the diverging asset.",
    "Step 3: Identified the high-low-higher high-lower low sequence and noted the down-close candle became a breaker block, a potential entry zone.",
    "Step 4: Chose to place the stop above the high that ran another high (high resistance liquidity) rather than just above the breaker, because CPI volatility and an unclean breaker required a safer stop.",
    "Step 5: Selected NQ over ES for the short — the asset that swept liquidity — since it provided the high resistance liquidity stop reference during a high-impact news release.",
    "Step 6: Zoomed into NQ to identify equal lows below as the downside draw on liquidity / target.",
    "Step 7: Entered short on NQ at the breaker/FVG/OTE zone with stop above the swept high and target at the equal lows.",
    "Step 8: After the displacement lower, suggested a potential continuation entry on a 1-minute setup using the 15m PD array, change in state of delivery, and a fair value gap entry to achieve a 2R target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade triggered; NQ respected the breaker block (body did not close over it) and displaced lower with significant range, validating the high resistance liquidity stop placement.",
  "lessons": "When taking SMT shorts during high-impact news like CPI, prefer the asset that swept liquidity so the stop can sit on high resistance liquidity rather than on an unclean breaker block. This protects against news-driven volatility while keeping the directional thesis intact.",
